> On Mon, 12 Aug 2002, George Lyle wrote:
> > Since this is just a financial transaction with the insurance company, you
> > still have the same title you've always had.  The check you get from the
> > insurance company is just smaller since they deducted what they
> > considered the "salvage value" from the total.

> This varies tremendously by state!  It is very local and something that
> each individual should inquire about locally.  Some states require a
> salvage (or other name implying really bad prior damage) as a cunsumer
> protection, others do not.  The threshholds vary as well.  If you have a
> bus "totalled" inquire locally before you sign anything!

I can see how it could vary from locality to locality.

Hereabouts, the declaration of "salvage" involves transfer of title to a
vehicle dismantler, not any transaction involving an insurance company.

